A dance of cultures, a homecoming of hearts. 💫
From global stages to Indian roots — @piasutaria ’s Origins, an @intabcpa Production, brings together ballet, contemporary, and classical Indian forms in one powerful conversation.

Our main man @hrishikay chats with @piasutaria Founder “Institute of Classical & Modern Dance” & “Indian Youth Dance Company”, Curator & Director “Origins”, @rchensee Master Teacher & Regisseur “Paul Taylor Dance Company”, @manishchauhan02 Dancer, Actor, Choreographer & Star of Netflix’s “Yeh Ballet" & @itsneerajlohni Contemporary Dancer Choreographer & Founder “Lohani Dance Theatre” about movement, identity, legacy, and the stories only dance can tell. 💃🌍🕺 pls go watch at the #jamshedbhabhatheatre @ncpamumbai this 18th of July 2025. Tickets are live @bookmyshowin and the #ncpa boxoffice

🎸 What were YOU doing at age 6? Kenny Wayne Shepherd was already obsessed with Stevie Ray Vaughan… and by 13, he was on stage tearing it up with his guitar!

This week on Live That Dream, @briantellis1 from 94.3 Radio One shares a candid backstage moment with the blues-rock prodigy during the Mahindra Blues Festival—where the chat went from guitars to growth, and even… Mel Gibson?! 🤯

Tap to hear how Kenny found his sound, stayed grounded, and kept chasing the dream—without ever losing himself.
